	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Miracle Piano IO is quite simple...</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Figured it out...  At least output anyway.
<br />First the game writes 00 to $4016 for the start bit
<br />Then does this 8 times:
<br />* Writes a byte out to $4016, only the least significant bit is received
<br />* Dummy Read from $4016 for some reason (why?)
<br />Writes a 00 to $4016 for the stop bit
<br />
<br />The bit order (after the start bit) is least significant bit first.  The 8 sent bits form a byte.
<br />
<br />The data itself is pure MIDI.  Looks like it could be easily integrated into any emulator.  It will probably need a special patch map, since the Miracle does not use general midi instruments.
<br />
<br />I'll bet MIDI input is very similar, start bit, 8 data bits, stop bit.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


